{{Quote|We've gotta call in the bombers!|A [[rebel trooper]]|<ref name="Battlefront">''[[Star Wars Battlefront]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Y-Wing-Fighter-SWCT.png|thumb|right|250px|A [[BTL-A4 Y-wing assault starfighter/bomber]], the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] bomber.]]
'''Bombers''' were [[starship]]s designed to strike heavily [[armor]]ed targets, like [[capital ship]]s<ref name="Malevolence">{{TCW|Shadow of Malevolence|Shadow of ''Malevolence''}}</ref> or ground artillery. Most of these ships were armed with projectile weapons, such as [[proton torpedo]]es,<ref name="Battlefront" /> [[proton bomb]]s,<ref name="ESB">{{Film|V}}</ref> and [[concussion missile]]s.<ref name="Ultimate">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> Even externally-mounted cargo containers could be used for bombing runs.<ref name="Iron Squadron">{{Rebels|Iron Squadron (episode)}}</ref>

In general, bombers were slow and ungainly craft, leaving them vulnerable to enemy starfighter attack. For protection, they often relied on both fighter escorts and each other. By flying in tight formations, bombers provided overlapping fields of fire, covering each other.<ref name="ICS">''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi: Incredible Cross-Sections]]''</ref>

